
[1]awning

   AWN'ING, n.

   1. A cover of canvas,usually a sail or tarpaulin, spread over a boat or
   ship's deck, to shelter from the sun's rays, the officers and crew, and
   preserve the decks.

   2. That part of the poop deck which is continued forward beyond the
   bulk head of the cabin.
